## What shipped (cp2)
- **`ReportCardService.enqueueArmRenderInTx(db, schoolId, userId, termId,
  classArmId, reportCardId?)`** — the enqueue mechanics (find cards → enqueue
  per card → flip PENDING → return count), composable inside another service's
  tx; writes NO audit (caller owns it). `enqueueArmRender` is now a thin
  withTenant wrapper that calls it + writes the render-batch audit. **Third
  *InTx pattern banked** (after `aggregateArmInTx` and the cp1 cascade/guard
  helpers): a method composable inside another service's transaction lives
  alongside its public withTenant-wrapping form. Inherits the slice-5 cp3
  properties — NO stable jobId (re-release re-renders) + enqueue-before-PENDING.
- **`ReportCardWorkflowService.release`** — PRINCIPAL_APPROVED → RELEASED +
  releasedAt + pdfStatus PENDING, then `enqueueArmRenderInTx` **in the same tx**.
  A thrown enqueue (Redis down) rolls the whole release back — no
  RELEASED-with-no-pending-render window (the plan-first "same tx" decision).
  Render FAILURES after commit do NOT roll back RELEASED (release is the academic
  decision; the worker flips pdfStatus → FAILED individually).
- **`ReportCardWorkflowService.reopen`** — OWNER ONLY (admin excluded per spec).
  Required non-empty `reason`. Rolls any non-DRAFT arm → DRAFT, **clears** the
  workflow timestamps (formReviewedAt/By, principalApprovedAt/By, releasedAt) for
  a clean re-walk but **preserves** the PDF artifact (generatedAt / artifactUrl /
  pdfStatus) — the R2 blob stays at its deterministic path and a re-release
  overwrites it. **Race guard:** any card pdfStatus=GENERATING → 409
  `ARM_RENDER_IN_FLIGHT` (don't roll a card to DRAFT while the worker is about to
  write GENERATED onto it).
- **Comment editing — split by grain (Q4):** per-card `PATCH /report-cards/:id`
  (`formTeacherComment`, owner/admin OR form teacher, editable in DRAFT /
  SUBJECT_REVIEWED) vs arm-fan-out `PUT /report-cards/arm/principal-note`
  (owner/admin, FORM_REVIEWED only, `updateMany` writes the same note to every
  card). The split makes the fan-out visible at the URL — a per-card PATCH that
  secretly fanned out would mislead.
- **Defence-in-depth:** both comment edits run the state-gate AND
  `assertNoReleasedCards` even though the state gate already excludes RELEASED —
  the redundancy catches a future state-gate bypass before it mutates a released
  card.
- Audit actions added: `report-card.release` ({…, fromStatus, toStatus,
  cardCount, enqueuedCount}), `report-card.reopen` ({…, fromStatuses[], toStatus,
  reason, cardCount}), `report-card.comment` (one shape, `field` distinguishes
  per-card vs arm-level).

